<item>
            <title>[LU-10700] lfs hsm_cancel file1 file2... may send cancels to wrong copytool</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10700</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lfs hsm_cancel file1 file2...&lt;/tt&gt; sends all cancels to the first copytool found for archive of file1. This is because of the logic in &lt;tt&gt;hsm_find_compatible()&lt;/tt&gt; and the fact that a hal has an &lt;tt&gt;archive_id&lt;/tt&gt; but a hai doesn&apos;t. This is not critical for the posix CT since it doesn&apos;t implement cancel. (Cancel &quot;works&quot; but it&apos;s ignored by the CT until a progress RPC fails.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
